manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MSI Business & Productivity MSI Business & Productivity specializes in home & commercial office computing hardware with a design emphasis on productivity and user comfort. For business professionals searching for elegant, world class solutions engineered with cutting edge components, premium reliability and refined aesthetics, MSI Business & Productivity offers a broad array of innovative products to ensure a competitive working environment. PRO H610M-G DDR4 Business Elegance The PRO H610M-G DDR4 is a business-oriented micro-ATX motherboard featuring the latest Intel H610 chipset that includes legacy-friendly display connectivity. Supports Intel Core 12th Gen Processors (LGA 1700) Turbo Gen3 M.2 slot 1 x PCI-e 4.0 x16 slot 2 DIMMS with Memory Boost: Dual Channel (64GB Max. / 3200MHz) 7.1 HD Audio with Audio Boost HDMI, DP & VGA Ports

H610 Chipset, Smart Cooling, PCI-e 4.0 x16 Supports Intel Core 12th Gen Processors The PRO H610M-G DDR4 motherboard supports 12th Gen Intel Core, Pentium Gold, and Celeron processors. Form Factor: Micro-ATXSocket Type: LGA 1700Chipset: Intel H610 Integrated Cooling Features Chipset Heatsink: Provides passive coolingFrozr AI Cooling: Automatically adjusts system fan settings based on CPU & GPU temperatures Fortified PCI-e 4.0 x16 MSI PCI Express Steel Armor slots are secured to the motherboard with extra solder points to support the weight of heavy graphics cards. Steel Armor also shields the point of contact from electromagnetic interference: 1 x PCI-e 4.0 x16 slot (with Steel Armor)1 x PCI-e 3.0 x1 slot

Reliable Performance & Connectivity Gen3 M.2 Connector The PRO H610M-G DDR4 motherboard features MSI's Turbo Gen3 M.2 slot: 1 x Gen3 x4 32Gb/s slot *Supports SATA 6Gb & 2242/ 2260/ 2280 storage devices Optimized Layout Design 2 x DDR4 Dual Channel (3200 MHz)8+1+1 Power Design with Core Boost: MSI's exclusive technology provides stable and strong current delivered to the core processor.Memory Boost: A fully-isolated DDR circuit delivers pure data signals for optimal gaming and overclocking performance. XMP profiles in MSI BIOS are MSI OC LAB tested and can be easily enabled with auto power settings for better stability. Stay Connected 1G LAN: A 1Gbps LAN controller delivers a premium network experience.USB 3.2 Gen 1 Type-A: Connect to devices and transfer files at high bandwidth rates: 5Gb/s.HD Audio: 7.1-Channel High Definition Audio with Audio Boost.Display Ports: Include HDMI 2.1 & DP 1.4 ports (4K/60Hz) as well as legacy VGA

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for a super budget system.
reviews.reviewText: It’s very basic but it has all the features you’ll need and enough connectivity to make me happy. Only complaint is that there are only 2 fan headers, 1 cpu fan and 1 regular fan, so you’re going to need a fan hub or splitter to get this to work with more than 3 fans.Bit of an update: the argb connectors don’t work and require a lengthy update of some sort where you have to bridge the pins in a certain order and whatnot, kinda lame ngl.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: While this board can work for you, I appeared to of gotten a defective board. I will say the worst part is the receiving of thr bios software on DVD disk. Which is odd. Though I did get a refund in a timely manner when I sent it back

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Motherboard for budget builds
reviews.reviewText: Used this for my i3-12100f + Gtx 1070 build. The box looks like the postman had a little too much fun using it as a football potentially... but obviously that doesn't dock points on the standalone product. It works very nicely and I would 100% recommend it if you're going for cheaper new parts. Just beware that if you plan on upgrading ram that it only has 2 slots, so it'll be a little difficult to give yourself a good upgrade path.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The only problem I had is the "Intel® Ethernet Connection I219-V" did not work with linux due to a checksum error. Stange because it worked on windows.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for
reviews.reviewText: I planned on using the product for a custom PC build. It was supposed to be new but it looks like a return with a ripped bag and missing a SATA cable. My review is getting censored so just buyer beware*Edit*Reached out to customer support and got the problem resolved in a timely manner and everything is working fine now. Great Motherboard for first pc build with argb connectors.

If you are looking for an entry level motherboard that will give some upgrade room then this motherboard should be a consideration. I used this mobo as part of the build I gifted ny godson and it has served him well. It will allow him to upgrade the processor if he sees fit.

Funciona muy bien, bastante básica la verdad, si estas muy justo de presupuesto está bien mi caso no fue ese si no que me adelante sin investigar mucho en otros modelos que si hay mejores opciones que luego vi cuando ya tenía la placa madre instalada, solo esperar para poder adquirir otra más adelante.

This motherboard is great and has all you really need, I got it for only $104CAD on sale about $65 cheaper than the MSI PRO B660M-A after tax, I paired it with an I3 12100F, GTX 1070 FTW, and a single 16gb 3200Mhz stick of ram for now, I just swapped it with my old motherboard and my performance in 3DMark and other gaming applications improved A LOT over my E5-2650V2 Xeon setup while allowing me to get full use out of my 1070, it worked perfectly out of the box and the XMP feature was already enabled allowing the ram to overclock to it's max speed of 3200Mhz, the other reviewer saying it's "Not easy to setup" clearly is inexperienced and doesn't know what he's talking about, which is obvious when he complains about no onboard video when he tried to pair it with an F series processor, which doesn't have an iGPU, it literally says right on the 12th gen F series CPU box "Discrete Graphics Required".
